                <head>126. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On June 7, the Governments of the United States and the Federal Republic of
                    Germany exchanged notes at Bonn which provided for a voluntary contribution
                    toward costs resulting from the maintenance of United States troops in Germany.
                    According to the agreement, the Federal Republic would pay DM 325 million ($77
                    million) toward the support of U.S. forces. For texts of the exchanged notes,
                    see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, July 15, 1957, pages
                    129–130.</p>
            </div>
